The designed system of Taylors Uni Smart Clinic is set to enhance Sustainable Development Goal 3 
by offering more students of the university access to healthcare services.
Most students find it hard to cope with the clinic appointments and have to wait long queues, following the normal rules and regulations.
This system aims to give an online clinic management platform where students can easily book appointments 
and check on the availability of the doctor as well as manage their medical data. Logging into the system also
allows doctors to see the appointment and update the consultation notes, and the administrators to control user accounts 
and track what is happening in the clinic.
The system is also supposed to minimize waiting time, enhance efficiency, 
and bring to the students a better healthcare experience by digitalizing the booking of appointment process.
